    "Body": " Loan Servicing Specialist III at Silvergate Bank La Jolla, CA 92037 ???????????? About the Job Silvergate is an innovative company with an established and rapidly growing Fintech practice. We help entrepreneurs within the digital currency, blockchain and Fintech eco-system to realize their dreams by providing banking, technology and consulting services that are on the bleeding edge of the financial services industry. Complete new loan boarding on loans originated or purchased by one or more business lending units serviced by the Silvergate Bank and sub-serviced by others.???????????? This will include general ledger entries/accounting functions associated with origination or purchase of new loans. Review next day reports of loans boarded by others to ensure proper general ledger posting and file maintenance associated with new loans. ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES General Board and process all new loans, purchases and modifications accurately and timely Board loans that are more complex in nature Create and reconciles construction budget prior to loan closing Review and process construction draws and recommends for approval Send system generated billing statements and notices to customers. Review ACH reports on auto debit customers to ensure proper automatic posting Process loan payments for loans serviced by Silvergate and subserviced for Silvergate Process various transactions on the loan with the appropriate backup and approvals Research and respond to both internal and external customer inquiries Monitor tax and insurance reports to ensure taxes and insurance are current for all loans serviced by Silvergate. Process any necessary disbursements or place forced coverage when necessary Reconcile good faith account held for new loans Preparation of daily and month-end reconciliations for loans Coordinate, obtain and organize requested loan information needed for ongoing internal audits as well as external audits performed by Silvergate Regulators and the Federal Home Loan Bank Prepare and provide accurate payoff statements to inquiring parties.???????????? Processing the loan payoff when funds are received. Once payoff has been applied ensure the necessary lien releases and UCC cancellations are processed. Send original loan documents and any payoff refunds back to customer along with their short year statement. Maintain strong knowledge of the systems utilized in Loan Servicing \u2013 including but not limited to FIS/HORIZON/Image Center/ Prologue/OTE Process and review transfers in MERS system as well as monitor ongoing transactions in the MERS system. Review daily exception reports and distribute to appropriate department for review Provide training and support to peers Participate and may sometimes lead projects for loan servicing Serve as backup when supervisor is not available Provide input for process improvements Maintain current knowledge of all federal and state laws and regulations, along with the Bank\u2019s policies and procedures Must adhere to the company\u2019s core values of Challenge Convention, Do What\u2019s Right, Take Ownership, Empower People, Exceed Expectations, and Cultivate Awesome all while keeping our \u201cWhy?\u201d front of mind. Our Why? Silvergate is the banking platform for innovators, and we believe in the power of entrepreneurs to create prosperity for our communities Not to harm consumers with any act that could be misleading, unfair, deceptive, or abusive in act or practice KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES Greater than 5 years of experience in Loan Servicing Experience processing commercial and/or residential mortgage loans Excellent written and verbal communication skills Proficient in Microsoft Word and Excel Detail-oriented Good organizational skills Knowledge of the complete loan lifecycle and how each role fits into the cycle Ability to work independently with minimal supervision Must have high school diploma, or equivalent BANK SECRECY ACT REQUIREMENTS Responsible for adhering to the reporting and recordkeeping requirements of the Bank Secrecy Act and Anti-Money Laundering rules and regulations, observing economic sanctions by prohibiting transactions as specified by the Office of Foreign Asset Control (OFAC), following the Company\u2019s customer identification program (CIP) rules, observing all Company policies and procedures relating to BSA, OFAC, CIP, and related acts, and participation in ongoing related training. WORK CONDITIONS Standard office environment with a moderate noise level PHYSICAL DEMANDS While performing the duties of this job, the employee is: Regularly required to talk or hear Required to communicate with customer and coworkers verbally and in writing Occasionally required to stand; walk Required to sit for long periods and reach with hands and arms Occasionally required to lift up to 25 pounds Able to read documents, computer screens, reports, other communications and have the ability to adjust focus and close vision Management reserves the right to add to, change and revise this description at any time.???????????? This description does not include any marginal functions that are incidental to the essential functions.???????????? Also, it does not imply that these are the only tasks to be performed by the incumbent.???????????? Employees are required to follow any other job-related instructions and to perform any other job-related tasks requested by their supervisor.???????????? Any requirement may be modified to reasonably accommodate individuals with disabilities. Silvergate is an EEO/AA/Disability/Vets Employee ", 
